	2.	Sandbox Execution
	‚Ä¢	Suspicious files are executed in an isolated environment to analyze behavior before allowing access.
	3.	Content Filtering
	‚Ä¢	Filters harmful scripts, macros, or embedded code from uploaded documents or forms.
	4.	Behavioral Analysis
	‚Ä¢	Detects abnormal or malicious behaviors (e.g., crypto-mining scripts, persistent cookies).
	5.	Automatic Definition Updates
	‚Ä¢	Ensures latest virus signatures are always used without manual intervention.
	6.	API Rate-Limiting for Security Scans
	‚Ä¢	Prevents abuse or DoS attacks by controlling the number of scan requests per user/IP.
	7.	Data Encryption & Secure File Handling
	‚Ä¢	Uses SSL/TLS and AES encryption for files scanned and stored to avoid interception or tampering.
	8.	Integration with DevOps Pipelines
	‚Ä¢	Automatically scans code during CI/CD deployment to prevent infected code from going live.
	9.	Incident Response Hooks
	‚Ä¢	Triggers automated actions (e.g., auto-ban user, notify support team, rollback file) on detection.
	10.	Geo-Tracking & IP Reputation Check

	‚Ä¢	Identifies threats based on location/IP reputation using threat intelligence.

